Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['bʌntiη]
*danh từ
 ■cờ trang trí
 ■vải may cờ
 ■(động vật học) chim sẻ đất

Anh - Anh
bunting
bunting1
■ noun a seed-eating songbird related to the finches, typically with brown streaked plumage and a boldly marked head. [Emberiza and other genera, family Emberizidae: numerous species.]
Origin
ME: of unknown origin.
————————
bunting2
■ noun flags and other colourful festive decorations.
Origin
C18: of unknown origin.

sentences.en: I need a knitting pattern for American bunting stars and stripes.
sentences.vi: Tôi cần một mẫu dệt kim cho lá cờ ngôi sao và sọc của nước Mỹ.

sentences.en: She built up the fire and drew her rocker near it, and she sat rocking Baby Carrie and singing softly to her,"By lo, baby bunting. Papa's gone a - hunting, To get a rabbit skin. To wrap the baby bunting in."
